4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would propose an amendment to the
6 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, relating to public
7 K-12 schools, to require each local board of education
8 to adopt a policy requiring that The Pledge of
9 Allegiance and a prayer be conducted at the
10 commencement of each school day in each public K-12
11 school.
12 This bill would authorize violations of this
13 amendment to be reported to and investigated by the
14 State Superintendent of Education.
15 This bill would require the State Superintendent
16 of Education, upon a determination that a local board
17 of education or public school has shown a continued
18 pattern of intentional refusal to conduct The Pledge of
19 Allegiance and prayer in accordance with this
20 amendment, to withhold 25 percent of state funding
21 allocated to the applicable local board of education.
22 This bill would also authorize the Legislature
23 to further reduce the funding to a local board of
24 education following continued violations.
