TO BE ENTITLED
29 AN ACT
30
31 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
32 of 2022, to require local boards of education to adopt
33 policies requiring each public K-12 school to conduct a prayer
34 and The Pledge of Allegiance to the United States flag each
35 day; to provide for the report and investigation of
36 violations; to require the State Superintendent of Education
37 to withhold state funding allocated to certain offending local
38 boards of education; and to authorize the Legislature to
39 further reduce funding upon continued violations.
40 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
41 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
42 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
43 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
44 (a) Each local board of education shall adopt a policy
45 requiring each public K-12 school under its jurisdiction, at
46 the commencement of the first class each school day, to do
47 both of the following:
48 (1) Conduct The Pledge of Allegiance to the United
49 States flag and give all students the opportunity to
50 voluntarily recite The Pledge of Allegiance to the United
51 States flag.
52 (2) Conduct a prayer, provided that no student may be
53 required to recite a prayer. The prayer may be broadcast over
54 the public address system and may be prerecorded or recited
55 live.
56 (b) Violations of this section may be reported to the
Page 2

(b) Violations of this section may be reported to the
57 local superintendent of education. The local superintendent of
58 education shall review the violation. If the local
59 superintendent of education determines the report is founded
60 and the violation is not resolved, he or she shall report the
61 violation to the State Superintendent of Education, who shall
62 conduct an investigation. If the State Superintendent of
63 Education, based on the results of the investigation,
64 determines that a local board of education or any school under
65 that local board's jurisdiction has shown a continued pattern
66 of intentional refusal to comply with this section, the State
67 Superintendent of Education shall withhold 25 percent of the
68 state funding allocated to that local board of education for
69 the following fiscal year. If the local board of education or
70 any school under that board's jurisdiction continues to
71 violate this section, the Legislature shall provide for
72 further reduction of funding to the local board of education
73 in the annual appropriation of education funds.
74 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
75 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
76 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
77 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
78 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
79 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
80 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
81 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
82 language; and translate effective dates.
83 END OF PROPOSED AMENDMENT
84 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
Page 3

Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
85 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284 and 285 of the
86 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws of this
87 state. The appropriate election official shall assign a ballot
88 number for the proposed constitutional amendment on the
89 election ballot and shall set forth the following description
90 of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
91 constitutional amendment:
92 "Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
93 of 2022, to require local boards of education to adopt
94 policies requiring each public K-12 school to recite The
95 Pledge of Allegiance to the United States flag and conduct a
96 prayer at the commencement of the first class each school day;
97 and to provide a mechanism for the withholding of state funds
98 from local boards of education that fail to adhere to this
99 amendment.
100 Proposed by Act ____."
101 This description shall be followed by the following
102 language:
103 "Yes( ) No( )."
104 Section 3. The proposed amendment shall become valid as
105 a part of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, when approved
106 by a majority of the qualified electors voting thereon.
